modules.name: Color
modules.comments:
This module provides types and functions for dealing with colors, such as
the conversion between different color spaces and color manipulations.

children.comments:
Equality between two `Color`s is checked by comparing the (integer) RGB
values.
children.title: eqColor

declarations.comments: The representation of a color.
declarations.title: Color

declarations.comments:
Create a `Color` from integer RGB values between 0 and 255 and a floating
point alpha value between 0.0 and 1.0.
declarations.title: rgba

declarations.comments: Create a `Color` from RGB values between 0 and 255.
declarations.title: rgb

declarations.comments:
Create a `Color` from RGB values between 0.0 and 1.0 and an alpha value
between 0.0 and 1.0.
declarations.title: rgba'

declarations.comments: Create a `Color` from RGB values between 0.0 and 1.0.
declarations.title: rgb'

declarations.comments:
Create a `Color` from hue, saturation, lightness and alpha values. The
hue is given in degrees, as a `Number` between 0.0 and 360.0. Saturation,
lightness and alpha are numbers between 0.0 and 1.0.
declarations.title: hsla

declarations.comments:
Create a `Color` from hue, saturation and lightness values. The hue is
given in degrees, as a `Number` between 0.0 and 360.0. Both saturation and
lightness are numbers between 0.0 and 1.0.
declarations.title: hsl

declarations.comments: The color black.
declarations.title: black

declarations.comments: The color white.
declarations.title: white

declarations.comments: Create a gray tone from a lightness values (0.0 is black, 1.0 is white).
declarations.title: grayscale

declarations.comments: Convert a `Color` to its hue, saturation, lightness and alpha values.
declarations.title: toHSLA

declarations.comments:
Convert a `Color` to its red, green, blue and alpha values. The RGB values
are integers in the range from 0 to 255.
declarations.title: toRGBA

declarations.comments:
Convert a `Color` to its red, green, blue and alpha values. All values
are numbers in the range from 0.0 to 1.0.
declarations.title: toRGBA'

declarations.comments:
Parse a hexadecimal RGB code of the form `#rgb` or `#rrggbb`, where the
hexadecimal digits are of the format [0-9a-f] (case insensitive). Returns
`Nothing` if the string is in a wrong format.
declarations.title: fromHexString

declarations.comments:
Return a hexadecimal representation of the color in the form `#rrggbb`,
where `rr`, `gg` and `bb` refer to hexadecimal digits corresponding to
the RGB channel values between `00` and `ff`. The alpha channel is not
represented.
declarations.title: toHexString

declarations.comments: The CSS representation of the color in the form `hsl(..)` or `hsla(...)`.
declarations.title: cssStringHSLA

declarations.comments: Rotate the hue of a `Color` by a certain angle.
declarations.title: rotateHue

declarations.comments: Get the complementary color (hue rotated by 180°).
declarations.title: complementary

declarations.comments:
Lighten a color by adding a certain amount (number between -1.0 and 1.0)
to the lightness channel. If the number is negative, the color is
darkened.
declarations.title: lighten

declarations.comments:
Darken a color by subtracting a certain amount (number between -1.0 and
1.0) from the lightness channel. If the number is negative, the color is
lightened.
declarations.title: darken

declarations.comments:
Increase the saturation of a color by adding a certain amount (number
between -1.0 and 1.0) to the saturation channel. If the number is
negative, the color is desaturated.
declarations.title: saturate

declarations.comments:
Decrease the saturation of a color by subtracting a certain amount (number
between -1.0 and 1.0) from the saturation channel. If the number is
negative, the color is saturated.
declarations.title: desaturate

declarations.comments:
The percieved brightness of the color (A number between 0.0 and 1.0).
See: https://www.w3.org/TR/AERT#color-contrast
declarations.title: brightness

declarations.comments: Determine whether a color is perceived as a light color.
declarations.title: isLight

declarations.comments:
Blend two colors with a specified blend mode. The first color is the
background color, the second one is the foreground color. The resulting
alpha value is calculated as arithmetic mean.
declarations.title: blend

declarations.comments: Defines the colorspace in which an interpolation takes place.
declarations.title: InterpolationMode

declarations.comments:
A range of colors that linearly interpolates between the two boundaries.
The interpolation uses the defined colorspace. For the HSL colorspace, the
shortest path is chosen along the circle of hue values. The total number
of colors can be specified.
declarations.title: linearGradient

declarations.comments: Linearly interpolate between two colors, using the specified color space.
declarations.title: interpolate

modules.name: Color.Scheme.HTML
modules.comments:
Sixteen named colors from the HTML 4.01 specification (except black and
white).
See: https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/types.html#h-6.5

declarations.comments: The given color plus a lighter and darker variant.
declarations.title: shades

declarations.comments:
Three colors, separated by 30° in hue and centered around the given
color.
declarations.title: analogous

declarations.comments: Three colors that are evenly spaced along the HSL color wheel.
declarations.title: triad

declarations.comments: The given color and two complementary colors, split by 30°.
declarations.title: splitComplementary

declarations.comments:
Four colors that come in groups of two pairs which are on opposite sides
of the color wheel.
declarations.title: tetrad

modules.name: Color.Scheme.X11
modules.comments:
X11 colors as specified by the CSS3 specification (except black and
white).
See: https://www.w3.org/TR/css3-color/#svg-color
